caption: Great place, and very welcoming staff! The food is delicious, and is done surprisingly quick. It is a bit expensive, but totally worth it! You get a great portion, and the food is done in time. Proper protocols are followed. Would recommend the pad see ew.
Very clean and welcoming spot. They offer big portions and for fair prices. I liked the menu a lot and the staff members were super amiable and explanatory. Highly recommended.

I love this spot so much! The flavors of each dish are aromatic and harmonious, the staff are super helpful, friendly and speedy. My partner and I had the whole chili red snapper. I'm still confounded how a whole fish can be so crispy on every inch of the surface, and moist inside, in a takeout box no less. The curry puffs are sensational, the tom kha is extraordinary. The eggplant with basil combines tender chunks of eggplant and veggies drowned in an umami sauce spiked with anise pungency of fried Thai basil leaves. Support this excellent local eatery- I hope we can dine in when safe.

I am loyal to their their shrimp drunken noodles, meatless pineapple rice, green curry and coconut sticky rice when craving dessert. I am happy to see this place thrived throughout 2020. Courteous customer service.

Ordered a lunch special today, pad Thai for ten bucks. Nice portion but it smells and tastes like friskier dried cat food. After eating a few bites I ended up giving it to my dogs. At least they had a nice meal. Not sure about their other food but I don’t think I’m going there again.

The owner here is so sweet along with the other people working here.  Their food is so delicious and prices are fair. If you are tight budget, you can try their food during lunch special which includes appetizer and main dish for less than $10. Dinner prices is about 1.5×- 2x but bigger portion.My fiance and I love this place and order their dumplings and fish cakes as appetizers. Our favorite dishes is green curry, pad Thai,  and pineapple fried rice. Their lanoi float which is Thai iced tea with ice cream is a must. I think the only thing I would like to see improved is the consistency of hours. Most of the time we want to go,  they are closed or on vacation which is disappointing.Other than that,  they are great and deserve 5 stars!

Great restaurant! The staff were super friendly and accommodating for all our needs. Despite only having two people, they made sure we were well attended to. My glass of water never was empty and the food came as soon as their kitchen finished. Everything was steaming hot and delicious.  We ordered the calamari and curry puffs. Calamari was fried extremely well, only complaint is that the sauce wasn’t enough. The curry puff was flaky and puffy with a mild curry flavor.  I ordered green curry and it had a nice spice to it. It wasn’t as sweet as some other thai places, but there was still a ton of flavor. The ingredients were plentiful and the portion was large.  For dessert, we tried the sticky rice. honestly, it’s a super different, probably niche dessert where the sweetness comes exclusively from the mangos. I wish they gave more coconut sauce, but it was still tasty!  Overall, great place for thai food around Bay Ridge. Looking forward to coming again!

I really like this place. In Bay Ridge it is one of my favorite thai food spots, if not my favorite. The place is really cute (great place for a casual date) and the servers are really nice. I only wish that they were on Seamless, so I didn't have to call for delivery every time (I would have given it 5 stars if they were), but other than I love it.
